<br>
Ok, my opinion is the original poster is right on all the line. He was even not hard enough on how pvp sucks for pure mellees. I am a lvl 55 rogue, blackguard, with ragebringer playing the Vallon Zek server since it opened. I have a long experience and frankly, until lvl 55 and epic, rogues are dead 80 percent of time in pvp. Now i happen to be almost at 50 percent. I am talking SAME lvl here.<br>
<br>
     1- The mellee range bug when pursuing someone.  Whatever that guy said about connection is total crap. Got a modem cable and no lag with real good cpu and i have to be in front of thoses casters running in same direction to actually hit them for a round before they change their heading and lose me behind a hill or by turning in cirlce leaving that &quot;ghost&quot; behind them. It IS a bug. need be fixed.<br>
<br>
          Now for rogues out there, dump that stupid rbf and use your thrown weapon skill. I can do 40 dmg deadly strikes with the shurikens. That normally does the trick in killing thoses runners, if they stop to cast, press the mellee attack button. Also a good way to keep track of caster since you can &quot;follow&quot; your shuriken, it will make you face automatically toward the opponent. Shurikens are great cause of fast delay (ragebringer will haste your throwing rate) If you have time, make forged javelins, thoses are for people you really hate.<br>
<br>
    2- Damage shields. Can't beileive i readed people whining it is useless against 2handed weapon. Dunno what you doing but if you can't channel trough 2handers, you missed your vocation. Against a rogue now, the stats that have been given in previous post giving statistics are TRUE. If you are a caster, you can virtually stand up to a rogue and look at him die on your dmg shield. <br>
<br>
      You want more? It happen to me more than often that some casters, druid in particular, channel trough my ragebringer and burning rapier in off-hand. You CAN channel trough it, especially when you know all you got to do is place one lower level nuke or dot cause your dmg shield does all the job.  Dispelling his dmg shield, lemme laugh, it will be his last buff and by the time you did it, he casted 2 spells and you done for it.<br>
Golem wand, ya, if you can afford the 120pp for 5 charges to debuff him, he will prolly simply gate away and laugh at your money loss.<br>
<br>
     Solution. Well there is none. throwing weapons are still BUGGED so you will still take dmg from dmg shield.<br>
Your best bet as a rogue is to keep hitting anyways and circle him or walking trough him trying to get off that backstabb that will maybe get you victory. That will help you win more than trying debuff with normal pumice.<br>
<br>
---------------<br>
Finally, it is from my view the major points that need be adressed in pvp. You will need to always drink sow potions too and have jboots rdy in case of dispel.  Pure Mellee will always be at disadvantage in pvp in most 1 vs 1 situations, casters got for most easy means of evading like shadow step and sow. If you get jumped in the open simply dont fight it, have a 120 mr to resist snares and head for zone. Zone and rezone if need be but don't bother. if he there waiting for you, hit a round while he start to cast and zone. <br>
<br>
     The trick for a rogue is not fight the battles you did not started, if he rdy your chances of winning are ridiculous and i killed more than my share of lighties. Don't forget its a bluebie world out there, lighties are for most xteamers and crap like that. You want even reconsider playing on pvp server at all unless it is a Daoc server. EQ is NOT a pvp game, as hard people will try convince you this can be done or that or bla bla, the engine is not made for that and Verant never ever did crap for what is a minority of the total eq population. The only sad thing is i made friends there and dont want to start all over.<br>
