<br>
About resists...personally I don't think we should have any resist stats at all.  I think spells should have a fixed sort of resistance.  I don't want nukes to be any weaker at all you understand just  would like them to work a certain amount.  Like a mage casting scars of sigil on a warrior of the same lvl should have the spell work as it does now as if the warrior had x lvl of fire resistance.  X being a number that would lead to balanced pvp play. There should be a fixed racial or class penalty or bonus for certain types of spells (for ice comet hits for 720 in pvp, say it hits for 400 on one particular occasion and 450 on another.  As a barb with a 10% bonus vs cold I might then take 360 and then 405) Maybe certain rare items would give a small bonus to the dmg taken.  Seems a lot easier to balance than dealing with a resist stat that changes a lot as more expansions and new gear comes out.  The resist debuff change seems a  poor solution to this problem.  This is not a suggestion for eq as it is certainly, just an idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uurshulgi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Urshulgi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/01 2:41:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Take me under</span><hr size=1> Take me!~<br>
