<br>
Although people with fast connections will call you a whiner, there is a MASSIVE difference between the effectiveness of a player on a dial-up and one on a dsl/cable.  Nothing can really be done to correct this, you're falling victim to the Quake ping syndrome in pvp.  It's not going to matter how good you are if you can't follow someone due to lag. Trust me,  a caster on a 28.8-32.1 connect like mine is just as screwed.  I try to kite someone and I still get backstabbed  when it appears that the person is in front of me.<br>
<br>
Anyways, just to toss the proverbial can of jet fuel on the flames, here's a statement that all you uber pkers will really love.  From my experience with 19 months of pvp, 14.5 months of that spent 50+, a lot of the uber pkers owe about 60% of their talent to connection speed and a top of the line system. Very few pvpers have truly distinguished themselves as being anything better than an average talent playing an unbalanced class with a good hardware/connect set up.  It takes way more  practice to melee pvp on a dial-up compared to broadband.  When you hear all about these rogues and shadowknights and monks and rangers, etc who are such great pvp talents there's a reason.  Shadowknights and rangers are two classes that really shine in pvp while being pretty useless in pve.  But why play one of those when you can be a rogue or monk and be highly desired for both pve and pvp?<br>
<br>
<br>
Oh, and btw a well played level 60 paladin is THE HARDEST person to defeat in one on one pvp.  Note that I said well played. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=518.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=518.topic&start=41&stop=45>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=557.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=559.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=518.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.threadControl?topicID=518.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=518.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=518.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstud